            <title>Friday Week 7 - The Law of Cosines</title>
<page>
        <objectives>
          <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Derive the Law of Cosines.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    USe the Law of Cosines to determine dimensions of triangles.
                </p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </objectives>
            <introduction>
                <p>
                    The Law of Cosines is the first of two tools we use when working with non-right triangles (the second being the Law of Sines). The best way to think of the Law of Cosines is as the Pythagorean Theorem with a correction term because the triangle is not a right triangle.
                </p>
            </introduction>

<paragraphs>
    <title>Deriving the Law of Cosines</title>
<p>
    Consider the labeled triangle below:
</p>
